            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>S. *In nomine sanctae et individue Trinitatis <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king #Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/127"
                            >Heinricus</persName> divina favente clementia quartus Romanorum <rs
                            key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus <persName key="#Abbots"
                            ref="#people/2189">Alberico</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbati</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Monks #Immunity #Imperial/royal_diploma"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2001">sancti Benedicti iuxta Padum</orgName>*
                        eiusque successoribus per ordinem abbatis <placeName key="#Abbots"
                            ref="#places/2723">cluniacensis</placeName> ibidem constituendis in
                        perpertuum. Sane credimus nos in huius vitae cursu feliciter imperare et
                        summae pietatis munere caelestis patriae gaudia promereri, si studuerimus
                        circa Dei aecclesias quae ab impiis opprimuntur opera pietatis exercere et
                        ipsas et earum bona unde Christi pauperes in eius servicio sustentari
                        debent, imperiali potentia nobis a Deo concessa conservare atque defendere.
                        Ea propter omnibus Christi nostrique fidelibus tam futuris quam praesentibus
                        notum fieri volumus qualiter nos omnipotentis Dei causa et ob regni nostri
                        stabilitatem et animae nostrae nostrorumque parentum perpetuam salutem
                        devota et exaudibili petitione <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2091">Cluniacensis <rs key="#Churches"
                                >aecclesiae</rs></orgName> cuius fraternitatem diligimus et habemus,
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs> sancti Benedicti inter Padum et
                        Larionem situm, abbatem et <rs key="#Monks">monachos</rs> qui modo in eodem
                        loco sunt Deo servientes vel post futuri sunt per ordinem cluniacensem, et
                        omnia bona eius mobilia et immobilia videlicet <rs key="#Islands #Churches"
                            >insulam</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Islands" ref="#places/2400">sancti Benedicti</placeName>
                        cum aecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2058">sancti
                            Floriani</orgName> et omnibus ad eandem aecclesiam pertinentibus.
                        Insulam quae vocatur <placeName key="#Islands #Churches" ref="#places/2402"
                            >Gurgo</placeName> cum <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2059">aecclesia eiusdem insulae</orgName> et
                        pertinentiis suis. <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2931">Casale
                            Barbatum</placeName> cumm aecclesia <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2062">sanctae Mariae</orgName> et <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2063">sancti
                        Laurentii</orgName>, earumque pertinentiis, <placeName
                            key="#Churches #Tolls" ref="#places/2476">Septingenti</placeName> cum
                        aecclesia <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2064">sancti
                            Michahelis</orgName> eiusque pertinentiis et cum <rs key="#Tolls"
                            >ripatico de transitu navium</rs>, decimam partem <geogName
                            key="#Curtes" ref="#estates/2050"><rs key="#Curtes">curtis</rs> quae
                            vocatur <placeName key="#Curtes #Churches" ref="#places/482"
                                >Burbassium</placeName></geogName>, cum aecclesia <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2003">sancti Johannis</orgName>
                        suisque pertinentiis. Locum qui vocatur <placeName ref="#places/624"
                            >Nucetulo</placeName>; <orgName key="#Hospitals"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2077"><rs key="#Hospitals">domum hospitalis</rs>
                            apud <placeName key="#Hospitals" ref="#places/275"
                            >Mantuam</placeName></orgName> cum pertinentiis suis; aecclesiam
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2067">sancti
                            Valentini</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#places/2932">Maringo</placeName> cum <rs key="#Landed_possessions"
                            >terris ab eadem aecclesia detentis</rs>; aecclesias <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2066">sancti Viti</orgName> et
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2004">sancti
                            Iusti</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2475"
                            >Medula</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis et terras quas predictum
                        monasterium ibi possidet; aecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2074">sancti Michahelis</orgName> de <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/2936">Cotorlione</placeName> cum
                        pertinentiis suis; aecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2068">sancti Benedicti</orgName> apud <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/77">Ficariolum</placeName> cum pertinentiis
                        suis; aecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2098"
                            >sanctae Agathae</orgName> apud <placeName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#places/80">Ferrariam</placeName>, cum pertinentiis suis.
                        Monasterium <orgName key="#Monasteries" ref="#juridical_persons/2075">sancti
                            Cipriani</orgName> apud <placeName key="#Monasteries" ref="#places/914"
                            >Venetiam</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis; aecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2076">sanctae Helene</orgName>
                        apud <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2938">Tassariam</placeName> cum
                        pertinentiis suis. <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2969"
                            >Concam</placeName> cum aecclesia <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2099">sancti Leonardi</orgName> et omnibus
                        pertinentiss suis. Locum qui dictur <placeName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#places/2970">Foculare</placeName> cum aecclesia <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2400">sancti Nicolai</orgName>
                        et omnibus <rs key="#Decima">decimis</rs> eiusdem loci; aecclesias <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2006">sancti Benedicti</orgName>
                        et <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2080">sanctae
                            Mariae</orgName> apud <placeName key="#Churches #Decima"
                            ref="#places/2414">Gunzagam</placeName> cum omnibus decimis eiusdem loci
                        ceterisque earum pertinentiis. <placeName ref="#places/2929">Caput
                            vici</placeName>. Villulam cum aecclesia <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2079">sanctae Mariae</orgName> et cum omnibus
                        decimis et pertinentiis suis. <placeName key="#Churches #Decima"
                            ref="#places/2417">Custellum</placeName> cum aecclesia <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2054">sancti
                            Bartholomaei</orgName> et omnibus decimis eiusdem loci. <placeName
                            key="#Churches #Decima" ref="#places/2930">Gabianam</placeName> cum
                        aecclesia <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2060">sancti
                            Andreae</orgName> et omnibus decimis eiusdem loci. Ecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Castle" ref="#juridical_persons/2061">sancti
                            Venerii</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/2900"
                            >Marceneta</placeName> cum medietate eiusdem <rs key="#Castle"
                            >castri</rs>, et pertinentiis suis; aecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2073">sancti Michahelis</orgName> de <placeName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#places/2935">Telliore</placeName> cum pertinentiis
                        suis; aecclesiam <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2090"
                            >sancti Bartholomei</orgName> de <placeName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#places/4">Lucca</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis. <orgName
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2087">Sanctum Martinum</orgName> in <placeName
                            ref="#places/2940">Colle</placeName> cum pertinentiis suis; aecclesiam
                            <orgName key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2071">sancti
                            Leonardi</orgName> apud <placeName key="#Churches #Dioecesis"
                            ref="#places/53">Parmam</placeName> et omnia quae predictum monasterium
                        in eodem <rs key="#Dioecesis">episcopatu</rs> detinet. Aecclesiam <orgName
                            key="#Churches" ref="#juridical_persons/2081">sancti Sixti</orgName> de
                            <placeName key="#Churches" ref="#places/361">Lecto Paludano</placeName>
                        cum pertinentiis suis; cclesiam <orgName key="#Churches"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/2069">sanctae Mariae et sancti
                            Johannis</orgName> in <geogName key="#Dioecesis" ref="#juridical_persons/80"
                            >episcopatu <placeName key="#Dioecesis #Churches" ref="#places/7"
                                >Bononiensi</placeName></geogName> cum pertinentiis earum. Decimas
                        de <placeName key="#Decima" ref="#places/2972">Roncis Guntardi</placeName>;
                        terras quas predictum monasterium detinet in <placeName
                            key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2410">Monticulo</placeName> et in
                            <placeName key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2971"
                            >Birupto</placeName>; cetera quoque omnia quae sepe dictum monasterium
                        nunc tenet vel in futuro adquisierit per hanc <rs
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">mundiburdialem paginam</rs> sub tutenam
                        nostrae defensionis suscipimus. Precipimus etiam ut nullus potens vel
                        impotens supradictum locum sancti Benedicti et omnia ad eum pertinentia sub
                        nostra defensione suscepta invadere presumat vel in aliquo molestare, sed
                        nunc et semper habeantur in secura libertate. <rs key="#Immunity">Si quis
                            igitur archiepiscopus, episcopus, dux, comes, vicecomes, vel alia
                            quaelibet persona, magna vel parva, cuiuscumque conditionis fuerit,
                            huius nostrae pietatis concessam libertatem in aliquo violare
                            presumpserit <rs key="#Penalty">mille libras auri boni</rs> compositurus
                                <rs key="#Tuitio/bannum/mundeburdium">banno</rs> nostro
                            subiacebit</rs>, dimidietatem <rs key="#Fiscal_property #Camera_regis"
                            >camerae nostrae</rs> et dimidietatem supradictae ęcclesiae. Ut autem
                        hoc ab omnibus firmiter credatur, et inviolabile permaneat, hanc cartam inde
                        conscriptam impressione nostri sigilli iussimus insigniri. [Signum Domini
                        Heinrici quarti Romanorum Imperatoris Invictissimi. <persName
                            key="#Imperial/royal_diploma" ref="#people/3513">Burcardus</persName>
                        vice <persName key="#Archchancellor #Bishops" ref="#people/3512"
                            >Alberti</persName>
                        <rs key="#Archchancellor">Archicancellarii</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Bishops" ref="#places/2968">Maguntine</placeName> sedis <rs
                            key="#Bishops">electi</rs> recognovit] (M). Data XIImo Kalendas iunii
                        Indictione IIII, anno Dominicae incarnationis Millesimo C. XI. Regnante
                        Heinrico quinto rege romanorum anno V, imperante primo, ordinationis eius
                        XI. Actum <placeName ref="#places/59">Veronę</placeName> in Cristo felciter.
                        AMEN </ab>
                </div>
            </div>
